Pre-heat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and @broccoli florets{200%g} on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{} , the @garlic salt{1/2%tsp} and the @dried thyme{1/2%tsp}. Season with a pinch of @pepper{} and mix together then spread out in one layer.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pop the chicken and broccoli into your oven to roast for ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a glug of @oil{} and add the @gnocchi{500%g}. Cook for ~{8-10%minutes} until browned and crispy.

> TIP: Do this in batches if necessary.

While your gnocchi is cooking, slice the @mozzarella{1}(sliced) into thin slices.

Add the @chicken stock powder{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml} to the gnocchi once they are golden. Stir together to dissolve the stock powder, then stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @onion marmalade{40%g}. Add your chicken and broccoli to the pan, stir everything together and bubble away for ~{2%minutes}.

Preheat your #grill{} to high. Lay the mozzarella slices on top of the gnocchi in your pan.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof then transfer the mixture to an #ovenproof dish{} and lay on the mozzarella once it's in there.

Pop the pan or #baking dish{} under the grill for ~{5-6%minutes} or until the mozzarella is browned and bubbly. Serve your gnocchi in #bowls{}. Enjoy!